As a mother of three baby boys and as a journalist, it has been heartbreaking to see all the children we’re losing to violence. There’s not one correct answer that will fix the problem. I only pray that collectively we can find effective ways to make this all stop. Many prayers to these families, you all are not alone in your suffering. In this story I interviewed two activists, one who was a former drug dealer who now has a program to help kids who are in similar circumstances. Thank you so much @makingthetransition  and @iamsharbates for your insight and all the hard work you both are doing for these children.

He went to the hospital and never came back home. No hospice care, no time to gather family or anything. That’s been the hardest part of mourning the loss of my grandfather. I thought I had time to prepare but that was taken away in a matter of hours. I was his very first grandchild in 1980, since then we’ve all lost count. But grandpa Robert leaves behind an incredible legacy. He worked hard all his life from the steel mills in Gary, Indiana, to owning an auto repair shop, to becoming a welder in Riverdale. He relocated before any of the grandchildren were born to start a new life for our family in a city filled with so many opportunities. Special prayers to my mommie and my aunties Ava, Wonda, Tichina, Thoenicia, and Temoka. He loved all of his girls. 

Thank you to everyone who has called, texted, sent cards and offered prayers. Thank you to Willie Watkins Funeral Home and the Georgia National Cemetery for your excellent service and for the comfort provided to our family during this time. We are so proud grandpa was laid to rest next to fellow marines and other men and women who have bravely served our county. #UsMarine #GirlDad #Grandpa

The last 18 months have been some of the toughest months of my life. From a difficult pregnancy, car accident while pregnant, partial bed rest, postpartum issues to even more weight gain.

All that combined makes winning these two awards extra special. As I slowly get back to my normal self, this was a personal win I needed 😭. I had been fascinated with the history of Oscarville for a while. It took months to track down descendants. Only with the help of Bob Mackey I was able to find a family willing to share their history. My photographer Tyson Paul worked above and beyond his scheduled shifts to bring this story to air. He shot several hours straight just to get the perfect sunset for a time lapse sequence that only lasted seconds. I won’t mention what he had to do in his backyard to get the perfect shot of a flame just to use as an overlay. 

We were determined to tell this story before I went on maternity leave. I remember being in so much pain going into the studio to tape a portion. A colleague walked over to me and kindly said “you should probably go home”. I taped my into and tag, went home, had another beautiful baby boy and the story went viral. 

It’s so rewarding to have this story shared so much online and on social media or to be at the store and have someone say “Did you do the story on the all Black town buried underneath Lake Lanier?” I’m truly honored and humbled by @nabjofficial National Association of Black Journalists and @atlpressclub for recognizing our team of journalists at 11Alive  who made this possible. Kristie Anderson Mk Richards Daris Schneider-Bray Kristen Brown Thank you soooo much!!!! 🙏🏾🙏🏾🙏🏾😭😭😭

I was expecting his beloved character ‘Maurice Webb’ from #SistasOnBET to walk into the studio. But instead, I got a chance to get to know Brian Jordan Jr., the actor, the Renaissance man, during this ‘Black Frost’ chapter in his life. I briefly interviewed him years ago on the Red Carpet when #TylerPerry premiered #Sistas and #TheOval on #BET at the same time. But during this interview, I was inspired by all the layers that comprise him, some of which we get to experience during his upcoming performance.

Jordan debuts his one-man show ‘Black Frost’ Friday, Dec 8th-9th at the @woodruffartscenter This groundbreaking performance, written, directed, and by him, walks us through the first chapter of his personal life and career.

We are so thrilled to have him on our show @thebusinessbrief Congrats @brianjordanjr on your success!!! We’re sending cheers and more blessings to come!! 
 Shoutout to @makeithappen_bob  and @heartlandmediafilms for shooting and editing this interview!!!

#HannahPayne is sentenced to life in prison with the possibility of parole for shooting and killing #KennethHerring. This happened back in May of 2019. Police say Payne witnessed a vehicular crash between Herring and another driver that didn’t not involve her. Police say after waiting for about 20 mins, Herring left the scene for what appeared to be a medical emergency. Police say Payne followed the 62 year old for about a mile, possibly trying to make a citizens arrest. At some point police say Payne shot and killed Herring while he was in his car. She will have to serve at least 30 of the 43 years in her sentence.

Seven days ago today, 20 minutes before going on air, we received the text to get to the hospital because you might not making through the night. 

The level of sadness I’ve felt since you left us is almost too much to bear. There are broken parts of my heart I’m not sure will ever heal. 

Before becoming wives, mothers and launching our careers, we were just two girls who became fast friends while working at Perimeter Mall. 

From pregnancies to promotions, with birthdays and Beyoncé albums in between, we’ve experienced every major life moment together. I don’t know how to not have you in my life. 

I’m forever grateful I got to hug you, sit and listen to your playlist and count your new freckles for one last time before you transitioned. 

As you already know, your circle will be here for Deshawn and the girls as long as we are breathing. I love you so much. Like your name, you were truly a Joy and blessing to us all.

Our family has lost way too many people the last nine months. God, please don’t take anyone else away from us. Rest in Peace Grandpa, Linda, my diva Deidra, Amya, Rico and now my Joy Joy.
